4 Types integer values in JAVA 

byte  - 8 bits   (-128 to 127)
short - 16 bits ( -32768 to 32768)
int - 32 bits 
long  - 64 bits


types of floating values in JAVA 
float f1 = 4.5f  [ 32 bits ] 
double d1 = 4.5  [ 64 bits ]

//Note for float need 'f' at the end of the number if you dont add f 
at end it will become double 

char c ='A'  - 16 bits 
boolean isTrue = false;  // true or false

Note:- if you are using finance calculation use BigDecimal.
